<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 4:23PM EST  by NWS Indianapolis</headline>
<description>...A SNOW SHOWER WILL AFFECT EAST CENTRAL DECATUR COUNTY...
At 422 PM EST, a heavy snow shower was located near Greensburg, or 8
miles west of Batesville, moving southeast at 40 mph.
Winds in excess of 30 mph are possible with this area of heavy snow
along with quick reductions in visibility to under a mile.
Locations impacted include...
Greensburg, Millhousen, and Newpoint.
This includes Interstate 74 between mile markers 137 and 144.
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time when traveling.</description>
